<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="181" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,1123,1582]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1375,1401]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is widespread throughout West and Central Africa being associated to the palm 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Elaeis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guineensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Elaeis guineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[324,465,1412,1438]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Borassus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[324,427,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Borassus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gomes Alves, M. G." box="[479,697,1411,1438]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" pagination="63 - 88" refId="ref25572" refString="Gomes Alves, M. G. (1959) Cetonideos da Africa portuguesa. Memorias da Junta de Investigacao do Ultramar, 8, 63 - 88, pls. 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1959">Gomes Alves 1959</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Antoine, Ph. &amp; Camiade, D." box="[707,998,1411,1438]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref22959" refString="Antoine, Ph. &amp; Camiade, D. (1995) Revision du genre Platygenia MacLeay et description d'une espece nouvelle (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae). Coleopteres, 1 (1), 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1995">Antoine &amp; Camiade 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schoolmeesters, P." box="[1010,1253,1411,1437]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" pagination="2019" refId="ref29791" refString="Schoolmeesters, P. (2019) Scarabs: World Scarabaeidae Database (version Jan 2017). In: Roskov, Y., Abucay, L., Orrell, T., Nicolson, D., Bailly, N., Kirk, P. M., Bourgoin, T., DeWalt, R. E., Decock, W., De Wever, A., Nieukerken, E. van, Zarucchi, J. &amp; Penev, L. (Eds.), Species 2000 &amp; ITIS Catalogue of Life, 2019 Annual Checklist. Available from: http: // www. catalogueoflife. org / annual-checklist / 2019 (accessed 12 January 2020)" type="book chapter" year="2019">Schoolmeesters 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Jerath, M. L. &amp; Unny, K. L." pageId="30" pageNumber="181" pagination="59 - 64" refId="ref26357" refString="Jerath, M. L. &amp; Unny, K. L. (1965) Larvae of six genera of Cetoniinae from eastern Nigeria (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 19 (2), 59 - 64." type="journal article" year="1965">Jerath &amp; Unny (1965)</bibRefCitation>
gave a very scanty description of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Afzelius" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[628,748,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Platygenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbata">
<emphasis box="[628,748,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">P. barbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae. The adult female was collected in Jemberem by LT in a fragment of moist primary forest (
<emphasis box="[593,626,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">e.g</emphasis>
. 
<figureCitation box="[642,722,1483,1510]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,183,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[202,1385,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. a, butterfly trap baited with banana and pineapple, Béli - Petaqui, GAB; b, yellow chromotropic trap baited with banana, Coli (Quebo), TOB; c, light trapping, Balana river (Mampatá), TOB; d, herbaceous and shrubby savanna, Béli, GAB; e, open forest, Coli (Quebo), TOB; f, primary moist forest, Canamina (Jemberem), TOB; g, clearance by fire to shift agricultural plantation, Coli (Quebo), TOB; h, artisanal charcoal sale, Buba—Tunani, QUN." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6280704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6280704/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Fig. 2f</figureCitation>
). The specimen had several phoretic Pseudoscorpionida. Some ecological data were provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Antoine, Ph. &amp; Camiade, D." box="[534,848,1519,1546]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref22959" refString="Antoine, Ph. &amp; Camiade, D. (1995) Revision du genre Platygenia MacLeay et description d'une espece nouvelle (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae). Coleopteres, 1 (1), 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1995">Antoine &amp; Camiade (1995)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Joly, C." box="[859,989,1519,1545]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" pagination="28 - 89" refId="ref26401" refString="Joly, C. (2018) Deuxieme contribution a la connaissance des Cetoniidae du Ghana, sous-familles des Cetoniinae et des Trichinae (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae). Lambillionea, 118 (1), 28 - 89." type="journal article" year="2018">Joly (2018)</bibRefCitation>
provided biodiversity information (
<emphasis box="[1396,1436,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">e.g.</emphasis>
abundance, habitat preference) for GHA.
</paragraph>
